Ethekwini Fire services says the police are investigating the cause of the fire. #DStv403 DURBAN - One person has died in a fire that broke at a block of flats at Durban's North Beach on Monday morning. The victim was a doctor who worked at Addington Hospital. Division commander of the Ethekwini Fire services, Nkulumo Dube says the police are investigating the cause of the fire. The victim's uncle spoke to eNCA and says he is puzzled about how the fire started. Division commander of the Ethekwini Fire services, Nkulumo Dube says the police are investigating the cause of the fire. #DStv403